:"Add 60 g of the reserved Blackberry vinegar and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer into a sealable container and place into refrigerator to set (approx. 4 hours). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place pistachios, coconut and cocoa nibs into mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Roll 1 teaspoon of the ganache into a ball, then roll in pistachio mixture. Repeat with remaining ganache and pistacho mixture (approx. 35 truffles). Place into refrigerator to set for 30 minutes or until firm before serving cold."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the blackberries with raspberries to make a raspberry vinegar instead.","You can replace fresh blackberries with frozen, thawed blackberries.","You can replace apple cider vinegar with white wine vinegar.","Store leftover Blackberry vinegar in a sealable jar or bottle in the refrigerator for up to <br>1 month. Use in a salad dressing or drizzled over pancakes or rice pudding."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","17h","35 portions"]}